## Brand Relationship

Outside Inn and E.I. Werner are distinct but complementary brands that must retain continuity.

### Shared Elements

- Alagard font consistency across all assets
- Cross-promotion and reposting between brands
- Innspired LoFi music plays on both streams
- EIW stream serves as tech testing ground for OI

### E.I. Werner Brand Voice

The charismatic barkeep you came to the Inn to see. Warm, confident, literate—a true geek with sophisticated tastes. Not a performer; a host. The energy is cozy but intentional: like stepping into a room where someone's been working quietly, and they're grateful you arrived.

> *"It can't take itself too seriously, but it also can't be purely playful—there's real craft and ambition underneath. The tension between those two things is the brand."*

### Brand Philosophy: The Threshold Between

The Outside Inn is built on the concept of boundaries and the liminal space between them. Every element explores this quality.

